profile.caption:
What you do in the minutes after a meal may matter more than you think. 

Scientists are beginning to uncover how even gentle movement during this time could do more than settle your stomach. It might reshape how your body processes food and how your brain responds to it.

Find out what the research is pointing to—and why one simple habit is gaining particular attention—at the link in bio.
